.TH MCFN 1 "JULY 2026" "v1.0.0" "MCFN User Manual"
.SH NAME
mcfn \- Intelligent NixOS configuration tool and orchestrator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mcfn
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mcfn
is a CLI utility designed to simplify the creation, management, and deployment of NixOS configurations. It targets both beginners (via Wizard mode) and power users (via Pro mode).
The tool generates modular configurations based on Nix Flakes, integrating Home Manager, Stylix for theming, and sops-nix for secret management.

.SH MODES
.TP
.B Wizard Mode
An interactive step-by-step guide for beginners. Automatically detects hardware, suggests desktop environments, and sets up sensible defaults.
.TP
.B Pro Mode
Provides manual overrides for every aspect of the configuration, including kernel parameters, QEMU flags, and custom Nix modules.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-pro
Force launch in Pro Mode.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-lang " [\fIen\fR|\fIru\fR]"
Override system language detection and use specified language.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-deploy " \fIUSER@HOST\fR"
Initialize remote deployment to the specified target via SSH.
.TP
.B \-\-build-iso
Trigger the ISO image builder based on current configuration.
.TP
.B \-\-test-vm
Launch the configuration in a QEMU virtual machine.

.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/nixos/flake.nix
Primary entry point for the generated system configuration.
.TP
.I /etc/nixos/configuration.nix
System-level configuration generated by MCFN.
.TP
.I /etc/nixos/home.nix
User-level Home Manager configuration.

.SH SEE ALSO
nixos-rebuild(8), nix-flake(1)
